# VibeForge Rules

- Read AGENTS.md before coding.
- Use Context7 for package docs.
- Use Sequential Thinking for complex work.
- Do not mark done if blockers remain.
- Use NocoDB for tasks, plans, schedules, logs, and context updates.
- Keep README human/open-source focused.
- Keep AI rules in AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, .clinerules, and docs.
- UI must feel like VS Code, not a generic dashboard.
- Never leak secrets from .env.local.
